# This is a placeholder for the application icon
# 
# To create a real Windows .ico file:
# 1. Create a square image (PNG or BMP) at least 256x256 pixels
# 2. Use an online converter or tool like:
#    - https://convertico.com/
#    - https://www.icoconverter.com/
#    - GIMP with .ico export plugin
#    - ImageMagick: convert icon.png -define icon:auto-resize=256,128,96,64,48,32,16 app.ico
# 3. Replace this placeholder with the actual .ico file
# 
# The icon should represent your automation builder application
# Recommended: A simple gear, robot, or automation-related symbol
# 
# For now, PyInstaller will use the default Python icon if this file is invalid
